   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>"Our father it is who writes to his sons, the brethren of the poll-tax (saying) Lo, (there are) 4 sacks of Mena the sack-weaver; they have been received by me in respect of his poll-tax. So give him his receipt and see to them all and let them be made at the rate of 4 sacks to the half solidus. Pharmouthi 18, indiction 11. Giorgios.;(2nd hd.) Kyros."</ab>
         </div>
